// @run
// @log 3
// @log 2
// @log 9
// Nested 2D fixed-array indexing composes today (ROADMAP B13 context): a native
// array-of-arrays is indexed by chaining native `array.get` — `m[1][0]` reads
// row 1 then column 0, with no `"[]"` trap involved. A nested write `m[0][1] = 9`
// likewise composes from a native row read plus a native `array.set`.
const m = [[1, 2], [3, 4]]
print(m[1][0]) // 3 — row 1, col 0
print(m[0][1]) // 2 — row 0, col 1
m[0][1] = 9    // native nested write
print(m[0][1]) // 9 — mutation read back
